user.name: MONTSERRAT M
snippet:
Una tortura, 2 días en un pasillo tirada.
Ni me pusieron suero! Y me dan resultados e indica tratada con sueroterapia? Perdón? Poner la vía xa nada le llaman eso.
Gente muy joven que tuvieron q consultar sobre mi enfermedad a otros q tampoco sabían.
La comida ya de traca ni pizca de sal (siendo hipotensa) y cafe con leche : un sobre de cafe soluble a diluir con leche helada!!!.
Sin contar la experiencia de mi padre q entra sano por una caida y fallece por "covid" y por corticoides pasó a ser diabético..hipertenso..etc.
No es lo que era parece un tunel del terror.
Ah cuidado porque a mi padre le desapareció todo lo que llevaba de oro y la bata!!!
Salvado a algun@ enfermer@ y algún médico.(poc@s) pues nefasto.
Sanidad o el hospital? Culpa???

extracted_snippet.translated:
Torture, 2 days lying in a hallway.
They didn't even give me serum! And they give me results and indicate treated with serum therapy? Sorry? Laying the road for nothing they call it that.
Very young people who had to consult others who didn't know about my illness.
The food doesn't contain even a pinch of salt (being hypotensive) and coffee with milk: a packet of instant coffee to dilute with ice milk!!!
Not to mention the experience of my father who came in healthy due to a fall and died from "covid" and due to corticosteroids he became diabetic...hypertensive...etc.
It's not what it was, it looks like a tunnel of terror.
Oh, be careful because my father's gold robe and everything he was wearing disappeared!!!
Saved some nurses and some doctors (a few), well, disastrous.
Health or the hospital? Blame???
